Milestone 2: CNN Model Design and Baseline Training

Main objective
Build the first complete training pipeline for image classification by implementing and training a transfer-learning CNN baseline (ResNet-18), then validating performance with reproducible metrics.

Model design decision
Although Milestone 2 originally mentioned a simple custom CNN baseline, the implemented baseline in this project uses pretrained ResNet-18 (transfer learning), which is more practical for dog breed classification with limited training data.

Why this design was chosen:
- pretrained CNN features improve convergence speed and baseline accuracy
- fewer training iterations are needed than training from scratch
- architecture is standard and easy to explain, evaluate, and extend

Implementation structure (what was built)
1) Model construction
- File: src/model.py
- Implemented build_resnet18(num_classes, pretrained, freeze_backbone)
- Replaced the final fully connected layer to match the number of dog breeds
- Added count_trainable_parameters() for quick model size reporting

2) Training pipeline
- File: src/train_pretrained.py
- Built full training/validation loop with:
  - CrossEntropyLoss with label smoothing
  - AdamW optimizer
  - top-1 and top-5 accuracy tracking
  - optional max-batches smoke testing
  - optional freeze-backbone training mode
- Integrated pipeline loaders from Milestone 1
- Enabled class balancing in training through WeightedRandomSampler

3) Checkpointing and experiment tracking
- File: src/train_pretrained.py
- Saved:
  - last checkpoint each epoch (last_resnet18.pth)
  - best checkpoint by validation top-1 (best_resnet18.pth)
- Logged training history to CSV and generated training curves (loss and accuracy plots)

4) Evaluation module
- File: src/evaluate.py
- Implemented standalone checkpoint evaluation on train/val/test split
- Generated:
  - loss, top-1, top-5 metrics
  - classification report (JSON)
  - per-class accuracy CSV
  - confusion matrix plot

5) Inference module
- File: src/predict.py
- Implemented single-image prediction with top-k breed probabilities
- Added readable breed-name formatting for user-facing output

How this milestone is easier for users/teammates
- End-to-end flow is clear: train -> evaluate -> predict
- Reproducible CLI commands with configurable hyperparameters
- Standard saved artifacts (models, reports, plots) simplify grading and comparison
- Top-1/top-5 and confusion matrix outputs make model behavior easier to interpret

